			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Title is dramatic, but I am a bit nervous if this is a real possibility. I am not on test server, I'm not a designer - I just watch Lucy and try and see whats coming. With what little use Call of the Hero is now, its becoming even more obsolete. 
<br />

<br />
The two primary uses for Call of the Hero, for me, are:
<br />

<br />
1) On raids I transport late comers from the zone in to the raid. 
<br />
2) Feign Death people that need to be towed back.
<br />

<br />
There are a few other times I use, but not many.
<br />

<br />
Heres the problem: Wizards are getting both <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=6094&source=Test" target="_blank" class="postlink">Secondary Recall</a> and <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=5953&source=Test" target="_blank" class="postlink"> Teleport Bind</a>. Secondary recall appears to be the ability to make a second bind point, that is AA activated. You could bind at say, Plane of Tranquility and Plane of Knowledge, and depending if you Gated or Secondary Recall'd you'd decide which one you would go to. Teleport Bind causes the wizards entire group to move to the wizards bind spot.
<br />

<br />
I see this as a problem. If a wizard is bound in Plane of Tranquility (Secondary Recall), and has a secondary bind point (Bind Affinity) at a safe spot near Coirnav, whats going to stop him from grabbing 5 people, Teleporting to the Bind spot, disbanding, Secondary Recall, and repeating? He gets 5 people to the raid spot in 2 abilities. He could even go as far as porting 5 wizards, letting them all bind there, then everyone gets back out. You would then have, within an instant, 6 groups of people, entirely buffed, at a spot they might not normally be able to get to. Could bypass alot of content with the ability to drop a decent sized force at one spot with very little risk (Instant Evac). 
<br />

<br />
This is all alot of speculation. I'm not considering that these abilities might have 3 hour reset times, or where bind points can happen. I do, however, believe it is something that might later become a concern. It seems to be an ability based more on travel mastery, rather then an evac, so it might have a very low reuse time.
<br />

<br />
Does anyone have more information on either ability that might dispell this possibility? I don't want this post to be set in stone or critisized - I'm just curious if anyone can give information to create a more clear picture of what this next expansion is going to offer, that may affect magicians.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
