				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">okay damn anyone that thinks CotH should be removed... that is HERESY i say lol
<br />

<br />
first off, i LOVE coth, period. 2ndly you obviously aren't out of the box thinking about what you can do with it lol.  Coth is AWESOME for GoD people!  you can't bind anywhere but Abysmal ffs... but you CAN coth in EVERY zone up thru sewer trials (havn't been passed there so couldn't say about farther)... and tha'ts exactly what I do!  someone in groups invis drops on their way to the trial but i'm safe at the sewer entrance, plink, coth'd... np, no rez and rebuff crap... 
<br />

<br />
Or... someone has to leave a trial... so do this.. have the person leaving Quit Exp, but STAY in group, w/in 1 min they are ported outside the zone in, drop 1 person in group but have them Stay in Expedition, make leader whomever was just ported outside, they invite the new person to group, you /dzadd <name> and when they zone in ya coth them, then the person outside leaves group, you reinvite the person that's In the Exp but not in group back and you're GTG!  (i know that sounds horribly confusing but think it thru, it's sooo easy!)  You dont hav eto start over, fight back to entrance, or hav ethem die and try to drag their butt by rogue (if you even have one) etc... 
<br />

<br />
as for coth'ing for raids... uhm yea hello? it's perfect for that!  for Yelinak (long as you have good CoV), Ring of Slime, Sontalak, Lendinara etc etc.
<br />
you coth them then buff up and yer all GtG!  i coth my group to the Chardok B entrance cuz i've hunted there so much i have Ally faction in Chardok, or i'll coth a rogue down to the Royals so he can pick lock and then i coth everyone else down to kill...
<br />

<br />
Without CotH i think as a class it would actually hinder us to an extent, i've been creative in uses for that spell, it's been used to do amazing stuff and i can't believe any mage would even want to be rid of it ever!  of course i'd LOVE an upgrade like 'group coth' or something, but dont even think of having it taken away, it's hardly become an obsolete spell...
<br />

<br />
one question though...
