				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">With CoH and any other player who knows how to play his class, my group can single every Kod'Taz named within an hour (I think 5 or so on a patch day within an hour was our best). This obviously works well anywhere else CoH is enabled.
<br />

<br />
Usually, the one doing the pulling is a cleric or enc, and often through un-pacifiable mobs. They throw a shout in group for CoH about 6 seconds before they need it, keep running, tag the named they want aggro with, CoH hits, adds go home.
<br />

<br />
Gets lost members to your group asap, or clears aggro when somoene's invis drops / runs into the wrong place in zone while traversing a zone.
<br />

<br />
Gets late people to raids, of course. Helps your guild when you're racing another guild to a mob, giving it the edge it needs to win.
<br />

<br />
Bottom line, I never have this spell unmemed unless the zone I'm in prevents its use. It would be like a cleric not bothering to keep CH up.<br />_________________<br />-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=844035" target="_blank" class="postlink">Darovan Almar</a>, Arch Convoker of Cynosure
