				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">While it can be a burden using CotH (dual CotH from qvic to tacvi anyone /groan), I would never want to see it go.
<br />

<br />
1.  If you box a cleric bot it is great to bring her stright to you where you need it (once you've invis'd to camp, etc...).  You don't have to worry about making sure she is running the right direction or is keeping up (selo drogomar vs. run 3)
<br />

<br />
2.  Great for clueless newbs who get lost.
<br />

<br />
3.  You never know when someone is going to get stuck in geometry.
<br />

<br />
4.  Great way to kill people you don't like.  Either CotH to someplace where they are KOS (and your aren't) or CotH to you while you are floating over lava or CotH the AFK over water when when they don't have enduring breath...  Tons of fun choices, just need to be creative
<br />

<br />
5.  Great for pulling or erasing aggro.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=653282" target=_blank>Casala</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.hneguild.com" target=_blank>Heaven and Earth</a>
<br />
Saryrn</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
